<plot>This film was made to coincide with the fiftieth anniversary of Partition. It tells the extraordinary story of Quaid-I-Azam Mohammed Ali Jinnah. One of the founders of modern-day Pakistan, Mr. Jinnah believed in human rights, women's rights, minority rights and, above all, the rule of law. This film is one of a very few that has attempted to tell the story of Partition from the perspective of Pakistan.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?379398</url></doc>
